<m:mi> AB1 </m:mi>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> + </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> W </m:mi>
<m:mi> BA2 </m:mi>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mn> 0 </m:mn>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-37">Let us now change the path for motion from A to B by another path, shown as path "3". Again, the total work by the conservative force for the round trip via new route is zero :
